  "original_title": "\u0b86\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bc1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd -\u00a0 \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ban demonstrations - Police demands rejected by courts",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Three requests by the police, which were brought before the Colombo Magistrate's Court today (8) to ban the demonstrations against the government, including President Gotabaya Rajapaksa and Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe, were rejected.",
        "Colombo Chief Justice Nandana Amarasinghe, Additional Justices Bandara Ilangasinghe and R.N.L. Justice Mahawatta rejected the demands of the police.",
        "All University Students Union, today (8th) and tomorrow (9th) are protesting, the Karuwathottam Police demanded that they be prohibited from entering many main roads under the jurisdiction of the Karuvathottam Police Station.",
        "However, on behalf of the All University Students' Union, the President's lawyers Saliya Peiris, Nalin Inradissa and other lawyers appeared in the group forum and expressed strong opposition to it.",
        "Saliya Peiris, the President's lawyer who presented the arguments, argued that the right of people to express their opinion, expression and assembly should not be allowed to be violated in view of the High Court judgment known as 'Jana Gosha'.",
        "In this situation, Colombo Chief Justice Nandana Amarasinghe announced that Karuwathottam would reject the request of the police.",
        "In this situation, the Kollubitti Police in the presence of Colombo Additional Magistrate Bandara Ilangasinghe put forward a demand and requested to prevent the demonstration that will be held tomorrow from entering the Kollubitti Police Division. They sought an injunction saying that if a crime occurs in the area where economic centers and foreign embassies are located, it will worsen the situation.",
        "However, the lawyers who were present in the forum requested the court not to prohibit the constitutionally granted rights as the police have full authority to act on it if a crime is committed.",
        "In this situation, Maligawatta Police Officer-in-Charge Colombo Additional Magistrate R.N.L. made a similar request. When presented before the Mahavattha, he too rejected the request.",
        "Already yesterday (7) Colombo - the court had rejected the request made by the Fort Police with the help of the Attorney General to issue an order prohibiting them from participating in the demonstration and entering the area near the President's House in Fort.",
        "Colombo Additional Magistrate Keminda Perera rejected the request made by the Fort Police to file a case B 22502/22 under Chapter 414 of Chapter XXXVI of the Penal Code, citing intelligence as evidence."
      ],
